-- Berkshire’s Manville Signs 12-Year Lease for Denver Headquarters
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2013-01-02T22:07:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/berkshire-s-manville-signs-12-year-lease-for-denver-headquarters.html
Johns Manville, the building-products
unit owned by  Warren Buffett ’s  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A) , signed a
12-year lease to remain at its world headquarters in Denver.  The decision to stay at the JM Plaza on 17th Street
involved “thorough evaluation of the economics and employee and
business logistics of several locations, including alternate
sites downtown and in the Denver Technical Center,” the unit of
Omaha, Nebraska-based Berkshire said today in a statement posted
online.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
